The paper deals with constructing spanners for a directed graph based on a disk graph, which involves metric spaces and distance functions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization and perturbation techniques, which could place it in the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which could place it in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category.
